Reasoning: The paper discusses the compatibility and interaction between adaptive modulation and coding (AMC) and hybrid automatic repeat request (HARQ) in wireless communication systems. This topic falls under the field of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also considers the impact of channel fading, which is relevant to control systems (cs.SY) and multimedia systems (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper discusses the reliability of communication in error-prone channels, which is related to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR).
